            <p>At InspireSphere, we value your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you visit our website.</p>
            
            <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect personal information such as your name, email address, and other information when you subscribe to our newsletter or contact us through the website.</p>
            
            <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>Your information is used to provide you with updates, respond to your inquiries, and enhance your experience on our website. We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties without your consent.</p>
            
            <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
            <p>We use cookies to improve your experience on our website. Cookies are small files stored on your device that help us analyze web traffic and tailor our content to better suit your needs.</p>
            
            <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We take appropriate security measures to protect your personal data. However, no data transmission over the internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure, and we cannot ensure the security of information you send to us.</p>
            
            <h2>5. Third-Party Links</h2>
            <p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these websites. We encourage you to read their privacy policies before providing any personal information.</p>
            
            <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal information. If you would like to exercise any of these rights, please contact us through our contact page.</p>
            
            <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be reflected on this page, and the updated date will be shown at the bottom of the page.</p>
